them, spend time in product analytics, conduct interviews, join sales calls. Anticipate changing needs over time so you can adjust your product strategy as needed.</a:t></a:r><a:endParaRPr sz="1200"/></a:p><a:p><a:pPr indent="-304800" lvl="0" marL="320040" rtl="0" algn="l"><a:spcBef><a:spcPts val="1000"/></a:spcBef><a:spcAft><a:spcPts val="0"/></a:spcAft><a:buSzPts val="1200"/><a:buAutoNum type="arabicPeriod"/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr b="1" lang="en" sz="1200"/><a:t>Stay informed on the market.</a:t></a:r><a:r><a:rPr lang="en" sz="1200"/><a:t> Subscribe to key industry news sources, pay attention to legal/regulatory changes, stay aware of competitors. Ask peers in your organization for tips on how to stay informed.</a:t></a:r><a:endParaRPr sz="1200"/></a:p><a:p><a:pPr indent="-304800" lvl="0" marL="320040" rtl="0" algn="l"><a:spcBef><a:spcPts val="1000"/></a:spcBef><a:spcAft><a:spcPts val="0"/></a:spcAft><a:buSzPts val="1200"/><a:buAutoNum type="arabicPeriod"/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr b="1" lang="en" sz="1200"/><a:t>Doing the right thing &gt; Being right.</a:t></a:r><a:r><a:rPr lang="en" sz="1200"/><a:t> Set your ego aside and admit when you’re wrong. Don’t go down with a sinking ship. Accept new information and modify your approach as needed.</a:t></a:r><a:endParaRPr sz="1200"/></a:p><a:p><a:pPr indent="-304800" lvl="0" marL="320040" rtl="0" algn="l"><a:spcBef><a:spcPts val="1000"/></a:spcBef><a:spcAft><a:spcPts val="1000"/></a:spcAft><a:buSzPts val="1200"/><a:buAutoNum type="arabicPeriod"/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr b="1" lang="en" sz="1200"/><a:t>Notice when stakeholders are losing confidence</a:t></a:r><a:r><a:rPr lang="en" sz="1200"/><a:t> in the strategy and get curious. Find out why. Decide how/if to pivot. Avoid the temptation to stick it out because of the sunk cost.</a:t></a:r><a:endParaRPr sz="1200"/></a:p></p:txBody></p:sp><p:sp><p:nvSpPr><p:cNvPr id="1406" name="Google Shape;1406;p253"/><p:cNvSpPr txBox="1"/><p:nvPr><p:ph type="title"/></p:nvPr></p:nvSpPr><p:spPr><a:xfr